          "type": "thinking",
          "thinking": "Good. So the key rules for this \"full_year_rule_audit\" are:\n\n1. **Budget cap rule**: Departments should stay within their annual budget. When cumulative expenses reach 1.0x the annual budget, no more reimbursement should happen without special approval. (Budget Management - Article 3, Expense Reimbursement - Article 13)\n\n2. **Standard cap rule**: Without special approval, reimbursement amount cannot exceed 1.0x of the standard limit. (Expense Reimbursement - Article 12)\n\nNow I need to get the department budgets to see if any departments have exceeded their budgets. Let me also look up the various expense type standards to understand specific limits.",
